$The lambda function can be represented in LaTeX syntax as follows:

\[
f(\mathbf{x}) = \begin{bmatrix}
\sum_{j=1}^{5} j \cdot \sin((j + 1) x_{1,1} + j) \\
\sum_{j=1}^{5} j \cdot \sin((j + 1) x_{1,2} + j) \\
\vdots \\
\sum_{j=1}^{5} j \cdot \sin((j + 1) x_{m,n} + j)
\end{bmatrix}
\]

where $\mathbf{x}$ is a matrix with elements $x_{i,j}$, and the resulting matrix has the same shape as $\mathbf{x}$. Each element of the resulting matrix is the sum of the product of $j$ and the sine of $(j + 1)$ times the corresponding element of $\mathbf{x}$ plus $j$, for $j$ ranging from 1 to 5.$
